headline: PCAR Q2 Deep Dive: Tariff Uncertainty, Parts Growth, and Regulatory Shifts Shape Outlook
summary: Trucking company PACCAR (NASDAQ:PCAR) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q2 CY2025, but sales fell by 15.7% year on year to $6.96 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.37 per share was 7% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
